         <abstract>
            <p>This paper's results on price movement patterns during the late 1970s confirm those of earlier research, but positive excess returns are found to be somewhat smaller and the dispersion greater. The smaller new issues premium is partially attributable to use of the NASDAQ average as the market indicator. A study of 102 firms from 1969-1973 and a similar number from 1974-1978 shows that average sales volume has gone from $8.3 million to $22.9 million, with median earnings increasing from $464,000 to over $1.7 million.</p>
         </abstract>
